## Creating table in mysql

create table is a statement used to create a new database in a mysql.
create table table_name( column1 datatype, column2 datatype, columnN datatype);

column parameter specify the names of the columns of the table.

datatype parameter specific the types of data the column hold.(e.g int, varchar)

renaming table in mysql 
# Mysql provides a useful syntax that can rename one or multiple tables in 
the current tables;
mysql>rename table yufan to limbu;

renaming multiples tables in mysql 
mysql>rename table yufan to limbu, bahadur to phombo;
 
# drop or deleting table in mysql
the mysql drop table statements
the drop table statement is used to drop an existing table in a database
mysql>drop table name; 

mysql>drop table yufan;

truncate table statements is used to delete the data inside a data table, but 
not the table itself.

truncate table name;
truncate table limbu;
